# Supply-chain SHA256 checksums for release dependencies.
#
# Format: HASH  IDENTIFIER
# (two spaces between hash and identifier, like sha256sum output)
#
# To obtain NGINX checksums:
#   curl -fsSL https://nginx.org/download/nginx-VERSION.tar.gz | sha256sum
#
# To obtain nFPM checksums:
#   curl -fsSL https://github.com/goreleaser/nfpm/releases/download/vVERSION/checksums.txt
#   Then find the Linux_x86_64.tar.gz entry.
#
# IMPORTANT: Every entry MUST contain a valid 64-character hex SHA256 hash.
# The verify-checksum.sh script will reject any entry that does not match
# this format or contains the word PLACEHOLDER.
# If a version is used in CI/Dockerfiles but missing here, the build will
# fail with "No checksum found" — this is intentional (fail-closed).

